            <title>[MCHECKSTYLE-37] There should be a way to put the suppressions file inside the checkstyle configuration and override it with the overriding properties file</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-37</link>
                <project id="12317223" key="MCHECKSTYLE">Maven Checkstyle Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is most useful when both m1 and m2 projects shares the same configuration files.  What happens is that the configuration have an expression, say &quot;checkstyle.suppressions.file&quot;, which will be overridden by the location of the actual suppressions file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
